# Agent memory (this project)

Persist learnings in **`.cursor/agent-memory/`** (version-controlled). Skill: **`spec-agent-memory`**.

## Start of work

1. Read `.cursor/agent-memory/_project/MEMORY.md`
2. Read `.cursor/agent-memory/_project/specs-index.md`
3. Read `.cursor/agent-memory/_project/learning-journal.md` (last 10 entries) if it exists
4. If you are a named subagent (`/backend-engineer`, `/architect`, etc.), read `.cursor/agent-memory/<agent-name>/MEMORY.md`

## End of work

Update memory with concise, durable facts:

- REQ/ARCH implementation status (update `specs-index.md`)
- Architecture and module locations discovered
- Test commands, failure modes, config/env dependencies
- Recipe used and outcome (`bug-fix`, `maintenance`, …)
- Blockers and lessons learned

## Rules

- Keep each `MEMORY.md` **under 200 lines**; use topic files for detail
- **Never store secrets** in memory files
- `.specs/` remains source of truth — memory is an index, not a substitute
- Remove or correct outdated notes

## HANDOFF

Include **Memory updated:** with paths when you changed memory files.
